             sworn. - I live at No. <placeName id="t18050424-84-crimeloc479">18, Cranbourn-alley</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18050424-84-crimeloc479" type="placeName" value="18, Cranbourn-alley"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18050424-84-crimeloc479" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18050424-84-off476 t18050424-84-crimeloc479"></join>; the constable, Hawthorn, brought the bonnet to me; I had seen it in the day, it was only made the day before, I am quite sure it is mine; I do not know how it went out of the shop.</p>
               <p>Q. What is it worth? - A. Three shillings and sixpence.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. I never went into the shop; a young girl lent me the bonnet, and I was waiting at the place till she came back.</p>
